    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="516"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2586: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-19T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received December 19, 2.12 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3561. Your 6264, December 11, 5 p.m. Foreign Office has received similar advices
                    from Tokyo. Although withdrawal of Japanese <pb facs="0650" n="548"
                        xml:id="pg_548"/> reservations, for which it continues to press as hitherto
                    reported, introduces [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] <hi rend="italic">sine qua
                        non</hi> of the proposed loan, the Foreign Office is inclined to consider
                    disbandment of Chinese troops as relatively unimportant especially if
                    elimination of reservations be secured but informs me that the French are
                    strongly inclined to press for disbandment, the first point on which they have
                    assumed so positive a stand.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Paris informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
